@prefix cosci: <http://cosci.local/ontology#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

cosci:KnowledgeDocument a rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Knowledge Document" .

cosci:contentPreview a rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:domain cosci:KnowledgeDocument ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string .

cosci:level a rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:domain cosci:KnowledgeDocument ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string .

cosci:status a rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:domain cosci:KnowledgeDocument ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string .

<http://example.org/cosci/README> a cosci:KnowledgeDocument ;
    cosci:contentPreview """# CoSci Knowledge Graph

Minimal machine-readable knowledge structure for Phase 1.

## Purpose

This directory contains the foundational semantic structures of the CoSci framework.

Current scope:

- semantic boundaries
- validation rules
- ontology model
- RDF graph generation
- graph validation

## Current Status

Phase 1:
- Markdown → RDF transformation
- Minimal ontology
- Type-scoped validation
- Semantic boundary enforcement

Not implemented yet:

- inference
- SHACL validation
- graph reasoning
- drift metrics
- CI/CD enforcement

## Discipline Principles

- Explicit semantics over impl""" ;
    cosci:level "Formal" ;
    cosci:status "stable" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-28T03:04:42.086691" ;
    dcterms:title "Knowledge Graph Overview" .

<http://example.org/cosci/semantic-boundaries> a cosci:KnowledgeDocument ;
    cosci:contentPreview """# Semantic Boundaries & Epistemic Discipline

## Purpose

This document prevents semantic inflation, conceptual drift, and uncontrolled abstraction inside the 
CoSci Research Framework.

Every future claim must be assigned to a clear epistemic level.

---

## Binding Epistemic Levels

| Level | Allowed Claims | Not Allowed |
|---|---|---|
| Formal | mathematically or logically provable claims | metaphor presented as fact |
| Implementable | technically buildable with current tools | unimplemented system claims |
| Empirical | measurable through tests or metrics | untested performance claims |
""" ;
    cosci:level "Interpretativ" ;
    cosci:status "draft" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-28T03:04:42.086916" ;
    dcterms:title "semantic-boundaries" .

<http://example.org/cosci/semantic-linter> a cosci:KnowledgeDocument ;
    cosci:contentPreview """# Semantic Linter & Validation Rules

## Purpose

This document defines rules that can later be automated to detect semantic drift, conceptual inflation, 
and epistemic boundary violations.

## Core Rules

### 1. Epistemic Level Assignment

Every major claim should be assigned to one of the following levels:

- Formal
- Implementable
- Empirical
- Interpretive
- Visionary

Missing assignment should produce a linter warning.

### 2. Restricted Terms

Restricted terms such as:

- transdimensional
- emergent
- cognitive
- consciousness
- lattice
- epistemic system
- algebraically grounded

requir""" ;
    cosci:level "Interpretativ" ;
    cosci:status "draft" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-28T03:04:42.087125" ;
    dcterms:title "semantic-linter" .

<http://example.org/cosci/semantic-validation> a cosci:KnowledgeDocument ;
    cosci:contentPreview """# Semantic Validation Layer

## Purpose

This document defines how future CoSci documents should be checked against semantic boundaries and 
epistemic discipline rules.

The goal is to prevent:

- semantic drift
- conceptual inflation
- unsupported claims
- metaphor-as-fact errors
- uncontrolled abstraction

---

## Validation Checklist

Every new document should be reviewed against the following questions:

| Check | Question |
|---|---|
| Epistemic Level | Is every major claim assigned to a level: formal, implementable, empirical, 
interpretive, or visionary? |
| Restricted Terms | Are restr""" ;
    cosci:level "Interpretativ" ;
    cosci:status "draft" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-28T03:04:42.087327" ;
    dcterms:title "semantic-validation" .

<http://example.org/cosci/system-map> a cosci:KnowledgeDocument ;
    cosci:contentPreview """# CoSci System Map

## Core Domains

- Research
- Governance
- Infrastructure
- AI Systems
- Knowledge Graphs
- Benchmarking
- Digital Sovereignty
- Open Science

---

## Strategic Objective

Transform fragmented technological knowledge into structured operational intelligence systems.

---

## System Principle

Every domain must be:

- interconnected
- traceable
- scientifically grounded
- operationally useful
- enterprise scalable

---

## Long-Term Vision

Build a sovereign European research and infrastructure intelligence framework.""" ;
    cosci:level "Interpretativ" ;
    cosci:status "draft" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-28T03:04:42.087529" ;
    dcterms:title "system-map" .

